  "prompt": "How do I learn to ride a bike as an adult?",
  "response": "Learning to ride a bike as an adult can be done with these steps:\n\n1. Choose the right bike\n- Get the correct size\n- Consider a bike with a lower standover height\n- Use a bike with adjustable seat height\n\n2. Safety gear\n- Wear a helmet\n- Use knee and elbow pads if needed\n- Wear closed-toe shoes\n\n3. Find a suitable learning location\n- Flat, smooth surface\n- Open area with minimal traffic\n- Grass or soft ground can help cushion falls\n\n4. Adjust the bike\n- Lower the seat so you can touch the ground with both feet\n- Ensure tires are properly inflated\n\n5. Learn balance first\n- Remove pedals (or use a balance bike)\n- Practice gliding and balancing by pushing with your feet\n- Keep your eyes forward, not down\n\n6. Practice basic techniques\n- Start with someone holding the bike\n- Learn to start and stop\n- Practice turning slowly\n\n7. Add pedaling\n- Reattach pedals\n- Practice starting and pedaling\n- Keep practicing in a safe environment\n\n8. Additional tips\n- Stay relaxed\n- Be patient with yourself\n- Consider taking a class or getting help from a friend\n\nWith practice and persistence, you'll learn to ride confidently.",
